# mandrel-bench environment — copy to `.env` and fill in real values.
# `.env` is git-ignored; never commit real tokens.

# Required: a fine-grained PAT (or dedicated machine-account token) with
# repository create/delete + contents + issues + pull-requests scopes. Used
# to provision and destroy the ephemeral per-cell benchmark sandbox repos
# (bench-sbx-*) — see bench/driver/sandbox.js and docs/target-architecture.md §5.
#
# LEAST PRIVILEGE: a fine-grained PAT cannot be pre-scoped to repos that don't
# exist yet, so in practice this token carries delete authority over every
# repo under BENCH_SANDBOX_OWNER — the in-process bench-sbx- prefix guard
# (createEphemeralRepo/destroyEphemeralRepo/the janitor all refuse any other
# name) is what actually bounds the blast radius, not the token's own scoping.
# Strongly prefer a dedicated machine account/org that owns nothing else of
# value over using a personal account's token here.
BENCH_GITHUB_TOKEN=

# Required: the GitHub account/org the ephemeral sandbox repos are created
# under. The reserved bench-sbx- prefix must be exclusive to this account —
# nothing else under it should use that prefix.
BENCH_SANDBOX_OWNER=

# Optional: overrides the janitor sweep's TTL (hours) — a leaked bench-sbx-*
# repo younger than this is left alone. Defaults to 24 when unset. The sweep
# runs at the start of every `npm run bench` invocation and via the
# standalone `npm run janitor` script (see README.md "Sandbox setup").
BENCH_JANITOR_TTL_HOURS=

# --- Retired (no longer read; presence emits a deprecation warning) ---------
# BENCH_SANDBOX_REPO_URL   — replaced by the ephemeral per-cell repo lifecycle.
# BENCH_SANDBOX_REPO       — ephemeral repo names are generated automatically.
# BENCH_SANDBOX_BASELINE_REF — the baseline is now the per-cell seed commit.

# Optional: notification webhook for run-completion alerts.
NOTIFICATION_WEBHOOK_URL=
